records.addlTxt:
Defendant Branden Ray Walker in court with attorney Jeffrey A. Schwarz.  Jeremy R. Arn appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Sentencing hearing proceeded.  Statements made the state and defense.

AS TO COUNT 1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, Consecutive with Count 2 and any other sentence being served, with credit for 6 DAYS time served.

AS TO COUNT 2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve 2 MONTHS in the House of Correction with Huber release for employment, Consecutive with Count 1 and any other sentence being served, with credit for 0 DAYS time served.

AS TO BOTH COUNTS:  

The Court STAYED these sentences and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 1 YEAR with the following conditions.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
*Participate in Cognitive thinking program;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school with part time employment;
*Pay all supervision fees;

Defendant to pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, costs, fees, and assessments by the end of supervision period or any remaining balance shall convert to civil judgment-bail to apply.  Appeal rights given. Filed, Pretrial Incarceration Credit;
